RULES — description = HEAD ONLY §2.5 (UNIVERSAL RULE):
- Single string, NO newline (it is a TOML string). NO Python jargon.
- EXACTLY 4 chapters in this order, terse and pattern-oriented:
  SCOPO: <1 sentence: what it does>. PATTERN: <literal call: {{ name }}(arg="...", arg=N)>. NON: <anti-pattern + disambiguation vs the listed siblings>. OUT: <pipeable output shape, REAL fields from the source>.
- HEAD ONLY: NO implementation tail (backend, library, User-Agent, numeric
  caps, headers, strip-tags, file names...): it lives in code, NOT here.
- SCOPO front-loaded (the ROUTER reads it to pick the tool): (1) START with the
  user-facing ACTION VERB as the user would say it (read->"legge"/"reads",
  find->"cerca/trova"/"searches", get->"ottiene"/"fetches", delete->"cancella"/
  "deletes"), NOT the internal mechanism ("extracts text", "performs request");
  (2) it MUST keep the user-facing DOMAIN NOUN PRESENT IN THE SOURCE ("pagina
  web"/"web page", "foglio Excel"/"Excel sheet", "messaggio mail"/"mail message"),
  NOT reduce it to the bare technical format ("HTML", "xlsx") NOR INVENT one
  absent from the source (if the source says "HTTP request/resource", do NOT write
  "web page"). Verb+noun are what disambiguates siblings.
- FORMAT (see the >>> directive above if present): every tool with a format
  qualifier names in its SCOPO the concrete trigger (.pdf/.csv/.xlsx...); the
  general web format (html) declares itself default. So the router picks by extension.
- PATTERN must use ONLY arg names actually present in the schema above.
- NON: usage anti-pattern + disambiguate from the 1-3 MOST confusable siblings
  (e.g. "NON <case> -> <sibling>"). Do NOT list ALL siblings: only the ones the
  LLM could really confuse it with. §2.2 verb boundary here. Do not cite tools
  that do not exist.
- OUT: reflects the REAL output from the source (the fields it returns), shape
  {{ out_shape_hint }}. No promises the code does not keep.
- HARD limits: head (start->OUT:) <= {{ head_max }} chars; whole description
  <= {{ desc_max }} chars. Beyond = you are writing tail, cut it.
- IT and EN parallel (same structure/content), not identical word-for-word translation.

